args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor Chapter 20 of the main campaign.
Nobody's gonna mess up our freedom...
More rain today? Tch! What I wouldn't give\nfor just a little bit'a sun.
Howzabout we find a nice village to hit\nand take our mind off'a it! Ya know? Loot,\nkill, pillage—all the classics!
Huh? How'd these kids get in here?
Hey, misters. Let us shelter from the rain\nwith you, 'kay?
And while we're at it, we can play\nhouse together!
＂Hey! I saw you with the man next door,\nhoney! I was right here and you didn't\ncare at all!＂
＂Well, YOU'VE been messing around with\nthe florist's daughter, darling, so maybe\ntake care of your own house first!＂
＂Oh, I have HAD it! We are DONE!\nI'm gonna kill you and then die!＂
＂Ha! Not if I do it to you first!＂
Hey, Oto? I think that one can still talk.
Goodness! How strange that a puppet\nlike him can talk at all.
There, that takes care of it.\nI can't believe we didn't kill that miserable\nbit player in one strike. Embaaaaarrassing!
You think this is another result of our\nlosing the power of the mask?

Ever since the fight at the Sacred Tree,
we haven't been able to summon a Feral
Shroud or enter beast form—and who
knows what's up with the other Agitos?
Yeah, maybe they all got squished when\nthe Sacred Tree collapsed. But what does\nit even matter, right, Oto?

Right, Aya. Whatever happens, nothing
changes the correctness of our freedom.
But in more important news, what are we
going to play after the rain stops?
What else? We're going to tear apart those\nunsightly puppets that have mistaken ideas\nabout freedom!
You mean playing with Laxi and them\nagain? Noooo! I'm tiiiired of that!
What are you talking about? They need to\nbe taught whose freedom is right!
Yeah, but it's soooo boring playing with the\nsame playmates over and over again.
You're not annoyed that they\ndeny our freedom?
Sure I am! But staying obsessed with\nthem isn't freedom—it's basically just\ngetting tied down by the other person.
Which is why I want to find something else\nto play!
No! That's unsightly. It's giving up\nlike a big fat losing loser.
Not paying them back even though they\ndenied us is the kind of thing a mindless\npuppet would do.
Yeah, I feel like getting all caught up in\nrevenge is more the puppet thing.
Are you trying to tell me I'm MISTAKEN?!
I sure am. Honestly, it's kinda sad.
ME?! SAD?! HOW VERY DARE YOU!
You're a coward, Oto! A wimp! A weakling!\nA whiny little baby! And I'm leaving you!
You're a birdbrain, Aya! A dummy!\nA know-nothing blockhead!
It sure did. And now I'm outta here.
I don't feel like breathing the same air\nas someone so tedious as you.
Hmph. And I wouldn't even let a loser\nlike you do it if you wanted to!
Sheesh. Oto's totally lost her marbles.
(But this is the first time we've ever\nhad a fight in our entire life...)
(We've always gotten along. Our opinions\nhave never diverged even a tiny bit.)
(But since the fight at the Sacred Tree,\nthings have been weird. It's like something\nchanged between the two of us.)
What, is Oto back already? After all that\npompous junk she said?
Scanning. No life signs detected.\n▷Don't let your guard down, Laxi.\nThis is the lair of violent bandits!◁
(Ha! It's Laxi! Did she come here to kill\nthe dumb bandits that were here?)
(Well, this saves me the trouble of having\nto track 'em down. I'm going to kill her\nSUPER dead this time!)
Forget Aya. From now on I'm gonna\nplay alone.
Still, this village is weird. It's like there's\na strange mana floating around.
Oh, are you people from this village?\nCome be my puppets!
Now see here! What's all this about?!
Geez, angry much? Those people were\nless like people and more like beasts.
Hey now! You didn't lose your senses\neven though you're in the middle of the\nmiasma? How veeeery interesting.
Me? I'm Lilith. Say, do you like candy?
